TY  - JOUR
AU  - Malamud, Ofer
AU  - Pop-Eleches, Cristian
T1  -  Home Computer Use and the Development of Human Capital *
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjr008
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 126
IS  - 2
SP  - 987
EP  - 1027
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper uses a regression discontinuity design to estimate the effect of home computers on child and adolescent outcomes by exploiting a voucher program in Romania. Our main results indicate that home computers have both positive and negative effects on the development of human capital. Children who won a voucher to purchase a computer had significantly lower school grades but show improved computer skills. There is also some evidence that winning a voucher increased cognitive skills, as measured by Raven's Progressive Matrices. We do not find much evidence for an effect on non-cognitive outcomes. Parental rules regarding homework and computer use attenuate the effects of computer ownership, suggesting that parental monitoring and supervision may be important mediating factors.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjr008
ER  - 



